    "Due to their versatility, GNNs have found applications in various fields, including computer vision, natural language processing, social network analysis, bioinformatics, and drug discovery, among others (Zhou et al. 2020).",
    "The increasing importance and application of AI and machine learning in drug discovery have prompted different review articles outlining various data sets, machine learning algorithms, and deep learning models developed to predict synergistic drug combinations in cancer (Torkamannia et al. 2022; Wu et al. 2022; Pearson et al. 2023; Kumar and Dogra 2022).",
    "For instance, Torkamannia et al.",
    "(Torkamannia et al. 2022) comprehensively reviewed a wide array of drug development data sources, encompassing biological datasets like molecular omics data, drug target information, and molecular interactions, as well as datasets containing high-throughput in vitro screening of drug combinations.",
    "Additionally, they presented an overview of the literature on computational methods designed for drug synergy prediction, broadly categorized into deep learning (DL), traditional machine learning (ML), and network-based methods."
